Parliament, Tuesday, 9 June 2020 – The Portfolio Committee on Defence and Military Veterans will tomorrow, during a virtual meeting, receive a briefing from the Department of Defence on progress regarding the devolution of responsibility for infrastructure from the Department of Public Works to the Defence Works Formation. The committee will also be briefed on the business plan of the Defence Works Formation.
	
	Details of the meeting are as follows:
	Date: Wednesday, 10 June 2020
	Time: 09:00
	
	Meanwhile, the Select Committee on Education and Technology, Sports, Arts and Culture will receive a briefing from the Department of Science and Innovation on its response to the submissions received on the Science and Technology Laws Amendment Bill [B 42B 2018].
	
	Details of the meeting are as follows:
	Date: Wednesday, 10 June 2020
	Time: 12:00
	
	Members of the media who would like to be part of the meeting to observe may forward their contact details to Mr. Mlindi Mpindi on +27817167329 for inclusion in the Parliament Communications Service Whatsapp group, where login details will be shared.
	
	Members of the public may get involved and follow committee sittings live on Parliament TV (DStv Channel 408), via live stream on Parliament YouTube channel and Twitter page on the links below. You may subscribe to the Parliament YouTube channel to receive instant notification of live feeds.
	
	Twitter: https://twitter.com/ParliamentofRSA
	Facebook: https://facebook.com/ParliamentofRSA
	YouTube: https://www.youtube.com/ParliamentofRSA ISSUED BY PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON DEFENCE AND MILITARY VETERANS, MR CYRIL XABA.
	
